Set 1

Roadrunner-> Dupree's Diamond Blues, Minglewood Blues, Bird Song, Tons Of Steel-> Supplication-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Uncle John's Band-> Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: Pitch Correction With correct pitch, this would be the best source.  Not sure why no boards or really good Aud.s have ever surfaced.  It sure was one of the more fun scenes to have been at.  Rain and all.  Mick Jagger narc chic are you still workin' it?

Best I'd say it's the best source, no qualifications.  The pitch in Minglewood doesn't seem even a quarter tone up from a generated E tone in Audacity (329.63 hz).  More like an eighth off.  That's well within normal tolerances.  Charlie Miller's released sources with more pitch variance.
